headlines.description: — James Harden and the 76ers watched plenty of their bad plays on film during recent practices. The clips magnified the results on the court.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden, Embiid lead 76ers past Pacers 120-106 for 1st win

headlines.description: — Another game, another close one for the Toronto Raptors. They're noticing a trend.
headlines.shortLinkText: Raptors clamp down on Miami, top Heat 98-90 for split

events.name: Orlando Magic at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson fired the ball ahead to Obi Toppin, who dropped it behind him to a trailing RJ Barrett for a dunk that capped what may have been...
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks keep Banchero, Magic winless with 115-102 victory

headlines.description: — The Chicago Bulls looked as if they were on their way to a blowout loss to the Boston Celtics. The game turned out to be a romp, just not the kind that it looked like it would be.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan, Vucevic lead way as Bulls beat Celtics 120-102

headlines.description: — Kevin Porter Jr. scored 26 points and Jalen Green added 25 to lead the previously winless Houston Rockets to a 114-108 victory over Utah on Monday night, handing the Jazz their first loss of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Previously winless Rockets hand Jazz first loss, 114-108

headlines.description: — Ja Morant and Desmond Bane scored 38 points each to lead the Memphis Grizzlies to a 134-124 victory over the Brooklyn Nets on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bane and Morant score 38 each as Grizzlies beat Nets 134-124

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Devin Vassell scored 23 points and Jakob Poeltl added 14 points and 14 rebounds to help the San Antonio Spurs beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 115-106 on Monday night.

events.name: Denver Nuggets at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Anfernee Simons had 29 points, including seven 3-pointers, and the Portland Trail Blazers won their fourth straight game to start the season with a 135-110 victory over the Denver Nuggets on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Simons, Lillard lead unbeaten Blazers past Nuggets 135-110
